'Whose idea was this?' Mr DiMario asks.

The boys glance at each other, neither one wanting to take the blame.

'Did you think this was a good idea? Who got the paint out?' their father continues.

Ryder, aged three, points at Sawyer, two, and blurts out that his younger sibling got the paints by 'building stairs with wooden blocks.'

Sawyer is seen covering his face with his hands as his cover is blown. However, Mr DiMario points the finger back at Ryan: 'How come you didn't tell him "no"? Who's the big brother?'

Ryder hangs his head in admission that he should have stopped the painting session.

