When he and his brother are asked if they deserve to be punished they look at each other and shake their heads.

Mr DiMario is then heard breaking into laughter as the boys' adorable faces prove too funny. 

He tries to resume a stern manner, insisting that the siblings are in 'big trouble' but his voice continues to waver. At the end of the clip he says that a clean-up operation will be taking place.

The boys' mother, Alecia, said the art attack incident occurred two years ago. To date the clip has been watched more than 800,000 times.

Mrs DiMario concluded in an email to BuzzFeed: 'I’m glad people see the humor in this and that so many were able to reminisce and relate.

'[It's] just a great reminder not to take ourselves or our children too seriously.'

